Class HumanSourceClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.keenon.lense.human_server.HumanSourceClient

  • public class HumanSourceClient
extends Object
    Created by keenon on 10/12/15. This manages all the communication complexity of talking to the server over proto, and exposes a nice simple interface of callbacks for the client to use.

    • Method Detail

      • createJob

        public HumanSourceClient.JobHandle createJob(String JSON,
                                             int onlyOnceID,
                                             Runnable jobAccepted,
                                             Runnable jobAbandoned)
        This lists a new job with the server.
        Parameters:
        onlyOnceID - this is for preventing multiple jobs referring to the same entity from being taken by the same worker. We want two *independent* labels for the same token, not the same person's opinion twice. To accomplish this, a worker can only do a single job for each onlyOnceID.
        Returns:
        a handle to the created job
